GRASKOP – A 31-year-old German national identified as Bianca Müller, who was touring the area, lost her footing at Lisbon Falls on Wednesday and fell between 30 to 40 metres.

She sustained a number of fractures to her body, but managed to escape with her life after rescuers hoisted her to safety. The rescue effort took three hours. An eyewitness who was at the scene, recounts the dramatic rescue in tomorrow’s Lowvelder. ALSO READ: Pediatric Care Africa pays a visit to Magalela